        "\n",
        "# Example 2 <br/> Numerical integration\n",
        "\n",
        "## Basic functions\n",
        "\n",
        "For general numeric integration in 1D we use `scipy.integrate.quad()`, which takes as arguments: the function to be integrated and then the lower and upper bounds of the integral.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.small}"
      ],
      "id": "2adac5c6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from scipy.integrate import quad"
      ],
      "id": "ec885e06",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "quad(lambda x: x, 0, 1)"
      ],
      "id": "24f5cabd",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        ". . .\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.small}"
      ],
      "id": "f5538538"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "quad(np.sin, 0, np.pi)"
      ],
      "id": "d53af24d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        ". . .\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.small}"
      ],
      "id": "10534316"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "quad(np.sin, 0, 2*np.pi)"
      ],
      "id": "654f1f90",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        ". . .\n",
